# Frontend environment (optional)
# Copy to .env and adjust when running locally (npm run dev).
#
# MUST match your backend port (see backend .env PORT=... or uvicorn --port).
# Example if backend runs on 8002:
# VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8002/api
#
# On Windows, prefer 127.0.0.1 over localhost for API URL if you see network/CORS quirks.
#
# Leave unset to use: http://<hostname>:8000/api
# Or set to your backend API base, e.g.:
# VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
#
# When using Docker, the image is built with VITE_API_URL=/api (same-origin).
#
# Dev ports (see vite.config.js / package.json):
# - Main app: http://127.0.0.1:3005/ (strict; fails if 3005 is in use)
# - Clean URL (no :3005): run nginx on :80 (see HOW_TO_RUN.md), then:
#     npm run dev:behind-proxy
#   Open http://127.0.0.1/ — do not set VITE_API_URL (uses same-origin /api).
# - Guest portal: npm run dev:guest → :3008 (avoids clashing with main)
# Optional overrides for admin portal links / careers redirect:
# VITE_PORT_GUEST=3008
# VITE_PORT_FREELANCER=3006
# VITE_PORT_EMPLOYEE=3007
# VITE_PORT_MAIN=3005
#
# With nginx on :80, portal URLs without extra ports:
#   npm run dev:behind-proxy
#   npm run dev:portals:proxy
# Then open http://127.0.0.1/guest  (and /freelancer, /employee)
#
# Without proxy, portals use http://127.0.0.1:3008/guest/  etc. (see vite.config.portal.js)
